The paper proposes a new type of spiking neuron model for event-based processing of neural networks, which is relevant to the field of neuromorphic computing (cs.ET). The focus is on image classification tasks, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses training methods and convergence rates, which are topics typically associated with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed method to state-of-the-art conventional networks, which suggests the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
